  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6520.54 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6500 (-8.1B) and positive gamma cluster around 6525-6545, dealers are likely in active hedging mode following the regime flip and GEX surge. The PIN regime suggests dealers will fade any move - they'll sell strength toward the 6525+ resistance zone where they hold maximum long gamma, and aggressively buy any dip toward 6500 where the -8.1B negative gamma wall creates amplified downside risk. Watch 6500 as the critical support level - a break below triggers dealer buying acceleration, while any push above 6525 hits heavy dealer selling pressure with the GEX flip at 6586 acting as the ultimate ceiling.",
